BEAM DEFLECTION CALCULATOR — VALIDATION STUDY
==============================================

Problem: Simply supported beam, point load at midspan
------------------------------------------------------
L  = 5 m
P  = 10 kN (at x = 2.5 m)
E  = 200 GPa (structural steel)
I  = 100 cm⁴

Textbook formula:
  δ_max = PL³ / 48EI
        = (10000 × 125) / (48 × 200×10⁹ × 100×10⁻⁸)
        = 1,250,000 / 9,600,000
        = 0.13021 m = 130.21 mm

